1
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:21,600
Is there no closer
community service?

2
00:00:21,667 --> 00:00:24,367
I can throw away
our neighbor's garbage.

3
00:00:24,433 --> 00:00:25,833
I mean that's still the same.

4
00:00:26,433 --> 00:00:27,533
We're here.

5
00:00:28,967 --> 00:00:29,933
Is this it?

6
00:00:43,700 --> 00:00:46,033
What can I do to help you?

7
00:00:46,967 --> 00:00:50,500
Promoting us is more
than enough.

8
00:00:50,567 --> 00:00:53,100
The truth is we know you.

9
00:00:53,167 --> 00:00:55,800
We know your mother, Lucinda.

10
00:00:55,867 --> 00:00:57,800
A lot of people here say that...

11
00:00:57,867 --> 00:01:00,567
you already forgot
where you came from.

12
00:01:00,633 --> 00:01:05,567
I tell them that one day
you will go back

13
00:01:05,633 --> 00:01:08,700
and introduce us to the world.

14
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:11,033
You know you should watch
where you're going...

15
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:12,600
Miss, do you own this road?

16
00:01:12,667 --> 00:01:14,967
Why? Do you own this road?

17
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:17,267
People from Manila are crazy.

18
00:01:17,333 --> 00:01:18,700
Can you help me?

19
00:01:18,767 --> 00:01:20,600
My boyfriend abandoned me.

20
00:01:20,667 --> 00:01:22,433
Can I borrow your phone?

21
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:24,433
There's no service here.

22
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:26,467
Let's just go where
there's a signal.

23
00:01:26,533 --> 00:01:27,767
I don't like this.

24
00:01:27,833 --> 00:01:29,300
Maybe we should call your dad.

25
00:01:29,367 --> 00:01:32,867
Mom, please don't. Please.

26
00:01:32,933 --> 00:01:36,267
He will just ask me
to go to his mistress.

27
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:38,500
If only I don't have
an important business meeting,

28
00:01:38,567 --> 00:01:39,600
I'll go there.

29
00:01:39,667 --> 00:01:42,467
Can you just trust me on this?
Please, Mom?

30
00:01:42,567 --> 00:01:44,033
I trust you.

31
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:47,300
Once my business engagement
is over, I'll go there.

32
00:01:47,367 --> 00:01:50,133
Wait, only locals would know...

33
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:52,167
that there's a signal
in this area.

34
00:01:52,233 --> 00:01:55,467
Me of all people,
I'm pure-blooded Uragon

35
00:01:55,533 --> 00:01:58,933
I know Bicolandia and all the
areas here that has signal.

36
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:02,433
You're exactly the right person
I'm looking for.

37
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:04,700
This is a surprise.

38
00:02:04,767 --> 00:02:08,200
Is Tiffany missing again
that's why you're here?

39
00:02:08,267 --> 00:02:11,467
Tiffany is out of town
for a school project.

40
00:02:11,533 --> 00:02:16,400
And I'm here now because
I want to talk to you.

41
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:17,900
Are you done being insecure?

42
00:02:17,967 --> 00:02:19,800
- I don't want to see your face!
- Bro, that's enough.

43
00:02:19,867 --> 00:02:20,867
Who the hell are you?

44
00:02:20,933 --> 00:02:22,933
I'm just the one
who promised her mom

45
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:27,167
that I won't allow a fool
like you to disrespect her.

46
00:02:27,233 --> 00:02:28,433
Is that so?
Do you want to fight?

47
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:30,100
James, what's with you?

48
00:02:30,167 --> 00:02:31,233
Is there a problem here?

49
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:35,700
Maybe you have forgotten,
this is my territory.

50
00:02:35,767 --> 00:02:37,767
James, let's go. That's enough.

51
00:02:37,833 --> 00:02:42,500
It will take years to be an
expert in making handicrafts.

52
00:02:42,567 --> 00:02:44,900
But with you, you're a natural.

53
00:02:44,967 --> 00:02:48,000
You are far better than me.

54
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:50,500
There should be a rhythm.

55
00:02:50,567 --> 00:02:52,600
That's the important thing.

56
00:02:52,667 --> 00:02:56,233
Not too fast and not too slow.

57
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:18,700
I don't want, someone might...

58
00:03:18,767 --> 00:03:20,000
- Hurry, come on.
- Someone might catch us.

59
00:03:20,067 --> 00:03:21,900
It's okay if someone catches us,
it will be more exciting.

60
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,967
I don't want to. The problem
with you is you're not serious.

61
00:03:24,033 --> 00:03:25,933
I'm leaving.

62
00:03:27,033 --> 00:03:29,933
That's the reason why we're here
because you're leaving, right?

63
00:03:31,467 --> 00:03:33,300
You're annoying.

64
00:03:33,367 --> 00:03:35,167
Can you even be serious
for once?

65
00:03:35,233 --> 00:03:36,267
I'll be leaving soon.

66
00:03:36,333 --> 00:03:38,000
We are going to graduate.

67
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,867
So what?

68
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:44,700
So how's that?

69
00:03:44,767 --> 00:03:45,900
What's going to happen to us?

70
00:03:45,967 --> 00:03:47,400
We'll have an LDR (Long
distance relationship).

71
00:03:47,467 --> 00:03:49,433
All long distance relationship
doesn't work anymore.

72
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:51,067
Eventually, they'll also
separate.

73
00:03:51,133 --> 00:03:55,400
No, our LDR is different.

74
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:59,533
As in 'Lang (No) Distance
Relationship.

75
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:07,633
Celeste?

76
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:09,033
Celeste, are you okay?

77
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:15,333
I'll go ahead.

78
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:18,000
Okay.

79
00:04:18,067 --> 00:04:19,600
Thank you so much.

80
00:04:21,767 --> 00:04:31,733
Thank you also.

81
00:04:36,733 --> 00:04:46,700
Thank you also.

82
00:04:57,967 --> 00:04:59,267
Are you done?

83
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:00,700
I want to go home.

84
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,367
Why? Is there a problem?

85
00:05:02,433 --> 00:05:04,167
I just want to go home.

86
00:05:37,133 --> 00:05:41,100
So that concludes our business.

87
00:05:41,167 --> 00:05:42,233
With your investment,

88
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:45,333
you are now a part of my group
of companies

89
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:47,200
as a minority stake.

90
00:05:48,667 --> 00:05:52,133
Now, Aurelia,
why are you doing this?

91
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,900
It's about Tonito.

92
00:05:55,033 --> 00:05:56,267
What about Tonito?

93
00:05:57,567 --> 00:05:58,900
I want him back.

94
00:06:01,367 --> 00:06:05,867
And I will do everything
that I can to get him back.

95
00:06:05,933 --> 00:06:08,867
And back to mine
and Tiffany's life.

96
00:06:33,167 --> 00:06:34,900
Are you okay?

97
00:06:34,967 --> 00:06:36,167
You seemed quiet the whole trip.

98
00:06:36,233 --> 00:06:38,500
Didn't you enjoy the community
service today?

99
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:42,633
Why are you doing this to me?

100
00:06:43,633 --> 00:06:45,833
Is that included in
my community service?

101
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:47,500
What do you mean?

102
00:06:47,567 --> 00:06:49,867
Why do you bring me
to those places?

103
00:06:51,100 --> 00:06:52,367
Are you doing it on purpose?

104
00:06:52,433 --> 00:06:54,567
You know that I have
a lot of memories there.

105
00:06:54,633 --> 00:06:56,133
Memories with my mother...

106
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:58,600
memories with you.

107
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:02,200
I don't know if you're just
doing it on purpose.

108
00:07:02,267 --> 00:07:03,433
But what is that?

109
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:04,833
You want me to remember
everything.

110
00:07:04,900 --> 00:07:06,767
- Maybe...
- Don't say it.

111
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:11,500
You know, I didn't decide
what you will do

112
00:07:11,567 --> 00:07:13,633
in your community service.

113
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:15,733
And believe it or not...

114
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:16,833
it was already prepared

115
00:07:16,900 --> 00:07:18,967
before they choose me
as your social worker.

116
00:07:19,967 --> 00:07:22,600
Now, you offered to promote
our area.

117
00:07:23,300 --> 00:07:26,967
Naturally, they included
that weaving area, right?

118
00:07:27,033 --> 00:07:29,233
I mean, you of all people know

119
00:07:29,300 --> 00:07:31,733
that the weavers of Sorsogon
are good.

120
00:07:33,567 --> 00:07:34,500
I'll repeat it, Celeste,

121
00:07:34,567 --> 00:07:36,033
there's nothing personal
about it.

122
00:07:44,867 --> 00:07:46,300
Good, that's clear.

123
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,433
It's really clear.

124
00:07:48,533 --> 00:07:50,667
You're the only one who is not
clear about my intention.

125
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:53,967
Is that what you've learned
in Manila,

126
00:07:54,033 --> 00:07:58,533
to be assuming aside from
wearing jeans all over?

127
00:08:01,467 --> 00:08:02,967
You know you can laugh
at me all you want.

128
00:08:03,033 --> 00:08:04,533
Honestly, I'm not offended...

129
00:08:05,433 --> 00:08:07,300
not anymore.

130
00:08:07,367 --> 00:08:09,967
I'm so done saying sorry
about being who I am.

131
00:08:10,033 --> 00:08:13,133
And whatever I accomplished
in my life,

132
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:15,467
it's because I've worked hard
for everything.

133
00:08:15,533 --> 00:08:18,700
From the smallest
to the biggest detail,

134
00:08:18,767 --> 00:08:19,967
I've worked hard for it.

135
00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:23,033
And yes, you know some people
will be happy for you.

136
00:08:23,133 --> 00:08:24,100
Some people won't.

137
00:08:25,967 --> 00:08:27,867
But I won't be affected by them.

138
00:08:27,933 --> 00:08:32,233
Honestly, the only opinion
that matters to me is Tonito's

139
00:08:32,300 --> 00:08:34,633
because he's there for me.

140
00:08:36,233 --> 00:08:38,533
During the time when I was going
through a lot,

141
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:39,933
and my world crumbled,

142
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:43,833
I got depressed
and he was there for me.

143
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:44,833
He didn't just lift me.

144
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:46,600
He gave me...

145
00:08:46,667 --> 00:08:47,967
wings to fly.

146
00:08:52,433 --> 00:08:55,900
And so whatever I am right now,
it's all because of Tonito.

147
00:08:59,633 --> 00:09:01,467
I'm happy that he came
into your life.

148
00:09:02,867 --> 00:09:04,633
I'm also happy
whatever you are now.

149
00:09:05,933 --> 00:09:08,867
But no matter what you say,
no matter what you do,

150
00:09:08,933 --> 00:09:10,067
you are still an Uragon .

151
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,267
Anyway...

152
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:18,533
I'm tired. You should rest also.

153
00:09:22,933 --> 00:09:23,767
Celeste?

154
00:09:23,833 --> 00:09:25,033
Wait, your phone.

155
00:09:31,833 --> 00:09:33,267
I'll make your daily report
later.

156
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:35,300
You already finished
thirty hours.

157
00:09:35,367 --> 00:09:37,700
Just keep a record of it,
so we're synchronized.

158
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:40,933
Do you need the crew tomorrow,

159
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:43,467
so I can include them
in the food budget?

160
00:09:43,533 --> 00:09:44,867
It's up to you.

161
00:09:44,933 --> 00:09:46,667
By the way, you don't have
to pick me up tomorrow.

162
00:09:46,733 --> 00:09:49,367
I'm okay, I can manage.

163
00:09:49,433 --> 00:09:53,767
Wait, why do you seem
to be in a hurry?

164
00:09:53,833 --> 00:09:54,833
Is your life running?

165
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:56,700
Yes, it's running.

166
00:09:56,767 --> 00:09:59,300
Sorry, I'm just used
to city life.

167
00:09:59,367 --> 00:10:01,900
Unlike here, it's like
the people are always asleep.

168
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,833
So you're saying
that we are lazy?

169
00:10:03,900 --> 00:10:05,400
No, I didn't say that.

170
00:10:05,467 --> 00:10:09,067
What I'm saying is that
the people here are laid back.

171
00:10:09,133 --> 00:10:09,667
Unlike in...

172
00:10:09,733 --> 00:10:10,767
anyway...

173
00:10:10,833 --> 00:10:12,867
You know, it's not too bad

174
00:10:12,933 --> 00:10:15,767
if you relax with your life
sometimes.

175
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:17,767
You know, appreciate things,

176
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:20,233
appreciate the people
who are important to you.

177
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:21,433
Yeah, very much.

178
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:23,767
I appreciate all the people
who are important to me,

179
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:27,633
especially Tonito,
because he didn't leave me.

180
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:38,567
You two are here.

181
00:10:39,633 --> 00:10:40,767
Are you all right?

182
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:44,567
Are you two fighting?

183
00:10:44,633 --> 00:10:45,633
- Yes.
- No.

184
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:48,267
We're okay, right?

185
00:10:48,333 --> 00:10:51,867
Celeste enjoyed her community
service today.

186
00:10:51,933 --> 00:10:53,700
Very much.

187
00:10:53,767 --> 00:10:55,833
Mikoy is very fun to be with.

188
00:10:55,900 --> 00:10:57,700
Anyway, I'll sleep very long.

189
00:10:57,767 --> 00:10:59,233
I will sleep the whole day.

190
00:11:04,733 --> 00:11:06,333
Mikoy?

191
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:08,433
Did my daughter really enjoy?

192
00:11:08,533 --> 00:11:10,367
Very much.

193
00:11:10,433 --> 00:11:12,567
It's not just obvious
because her makeup is thick.

194
00:11:12,633 --> 00:11:14,200
She can't smile.

195
00:11:15,567 --> 00:11:17,633
I'll go ahead.

196
00:11:17,700 --> 00:11:18,767
Take care.

197
00:11:32,767 --> 00:11:37,267
What? Did you get a car for me
for my stay here in Sorsogon?

198
00:11:37,333 --> 00:11:40,200
I'm arranging it now for you.

199
00:11:40,267 --> 00:11:43,367
Celeste, don't be stubborn.

200
00:11:43,467 --> 00:11:47,167
You should agree to have a
driver to avoid any accidents.

201
00:11:47,233 --> 00:11:51,333
I don't want to be with Mikoy.

202
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:53,533
Why?

203
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:54,900
I'm irritated with him.

204
00:11:54,967 --> 00:11:56,767
He's so "know it all".

205
00:11:56,833 --> 00:11:58,933
He told me "I know
the real you".

206
00:11:59,000 --> 00:11:59,967
What's that?

207
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:04,867
Why are you laughing?

208
00:12:04,933 --> 00:12:07,233
I'm more like thrilled.

209
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:09,300
Why are you thrilled, girl?

210
00:12:09,367 --> 00:12:12,400
Why do you think Mikoy is taking
you to familiar places?

211
00:12:12,467 --> 00:12:15,867
Dear, of course,
that was assigned to him.

212
00:12:15,967 --> 00:12:17,433
Come on, Celeste.

213
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:20,600
I know you're naive sometimes,
but you're not stupid.

214
00:12:20,667 --> 00:12:22,667
He still likes you.

215
00:12:22,733 --> 00:12:26,767
If you were to ask me, maybe he
hasn't moved on from you yet.

216
00:12:26,833 --> 00:12:30,733
Actually, I thought about that,
but of course, I ignored it.

217
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:32,667
He told me that
it's nothing personal.

218
00:12:32,733 --> 00:12:34,267
It's just work.

219
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:35,700
That's it.

220
00:12:35,767 --> 00:12:37,000
Good.

221
00:12:37,067 --> 00:12:38,167
Maybe that's why
you're pissed off

222
00:12:38,233 --> 00:12:40,567
because he told you upfront
that he didn't like you.

223
00:12:40,633 --> 00:12:41,700
What's with you?

224
00:12:41,767 --> 00:12:44,200
Why should I be irritated
if Mikoy doesn't like me?

225
00:12:44,267 --> 00:12:47,800
Please, I'm getting married
to Tonito.

226
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:54,600
And besides, oh my God, Mikoy
is no match to Tonito, please.

227
00:12:54,667 --> 00:12:56,067
You know there's no sense
talking to you.

228
00:12:56,133 --> 00:12:58,033
You should go back to work.

229
00:13:29,300 --> 00:13:31,900
- I don't want, someone might...
- Huh?

230
00:13:31,967 --> 00:13:34,333
- Hurry, come on.
- Someone might catch us.

231
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:37,067
It's okay if someone catches us,
it will be more exciting.

232
00:13:37,133 --> 00:13:39,067
I don't want to. The problem
with you is you're not serious.

233
00:13:39,133 --> 00:13:40,633
I'm leaving.

234
00:13:42,033 --> 00:13:44,833
That's the reason why we're here
because you're leaving, right?

235
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,367
You're annoying.

236
00:13:47,433 --> 00:13:50,200
Can you even be serious
for once?

237
00:13:50,267 --> 00:13:51,233
I'll be leaving soon.

238
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:52,900
We are going to graduate.

239
00:13:54,233 --> 00:13:55,633
So what?

240
00:13:58,100 --> 00:13:59,667
So how's that?

241
00:13:59,733 --> 00:14:00,867
What's going to happen to us?

242
00:14:00,933 --> 00:14:02,500
We'll have an LDR (long
distance relationship).

243
00:14:02,567 --> 00:14:04,400
All long distance relationship
doesn't work anymore.

244
00:14:04,467 --> 00:14:06,133
Eventually,
they'll also separate.

245
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:10,367
No, our LDR is different.

246
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:14,300
As in, 'Lang (No)
Distance Relationship.

247
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:17,133
You're really annoying.
No, I'm serious.

248
00:14:17,967 --> 00:14:20,000
Ours is 'Lang (No) distance.

249
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:21,500
'Lang distance?

250
00:14:21,567 --> 00:14:24,267
- What is that?
- It means there's no distance.

251
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:26,100
You know, you always
joke around.

252
00:14:26,167 --> 00:14:28,400
It's like you're not serious
about us.

253
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:31,267
Won't you let me finish
with what I'm about to say?

254
00:14:31,333 --> 00:14:32,767
Don't touch me.

255
00:14:32,833 --> 00:14:35,967
Wait, you're not letting me
finish.

256
00:14:40,133 --> 00:14:41,700
I applied in Manila.

257
00:14:44,667 --> 00:14:49,400
And I have a few interviews
lined up, so...

258
00:14:51,233 --> 00:14:52,567
I will come with you.

259
00:14:52,633 --> 00:14:55,967
But you like it here
in Sorsogon?

260
00:14:56,033 --> 00:15:00,733
But there are a lot of
opportunities in Manila.

261
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:03,267
Maybe someone will hire me
there.

262
